description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to join a specialist team providing a valued service? Do you enjoy working independently but like to know that you have a strong and supportive team behind you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;North Stoke CAMHS are part of the Stoke Community Directorate delivering intensive interventions with children and young people and their families experiencing emotional, behaviour and mental health difficulties across Tier 3 Health Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Community Mental Health Nurse who enjoys working with children, young people and their families, thrives on working creatively and wants to belong to a large and friendly multi-disciplinary team. We value our staff and provide regular clinical supervision, on-going in-house training and are flexible in relation to family commitments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity to work in the Community, gaining skills in assessment, care planning and risk assessment under the supervision of the Team Leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jane Sheldon&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;janeA.sheldon@combined.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
